cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.SD. 

The paper deals with end-to-end code-switching speech recognition, which involves natural language processing and speech recognition. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a new model for speech recognition, which falls under cs.SD (Sound). The use of language identity information and recurrent neural networks also suggests the possibility of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed method on a specific corpus, which could also fit under cs.SD.
